==English==

===Etymology===
from Greek ''Φιλοσοφία'': ''Φιλοσ'' (''philos'') = love + ''σοφία'' (''sophia'') = wisdom

===Noun===
'''philosophy'''  {{uncountable}}

# A comprehensive system of belief that is, generally, divided into five major subtopics:  [[Logic]]; [[Metaphysics]]; [[Epistemology]]; [[Ethics]]; and [[Esthetics]]
# A general principle (usually moral)

